 The protocol they follow, is as follows.
 Say A uses this setup, only to receive signals.
 If B wants to send a signal to A, all that he needs to do, is to disturb
 his particle at 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

.
 This would cause some change in, either the wavefunction or the position,
 or both, of the particle, compared to if B had not caused any disturbance.
 Now B measures her particle's position at 
\begin_inset Formula $t+\epsilon$
\end_inset

 and gets the value 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{B}$
\end_inset

.
 She knows what position her particle should've been at, if B didn't do
 anything, call this position 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{B}^{(0)}$
\end_inset

.
